                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d187">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/2094: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile (<persName corresp="#p_CWS1"
                            type="from">Culbertson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-08-18T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >August 18, 1932—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 6:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>175. Chile is not a party to the proposal referred to in your circular of August
                    18, 1 p.m., nor had the Chilean Foreign Office any knowledge of it prior to my
                    inquiry.</p>
                <p>The Minister for Foreign Affairs stated the position of his Government in his
                    number 73, August 12, which the Chilean Ambassador in Washington no doubt
                    communicated to you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CWS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
